  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for Life - Amazon case study 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The case study is part of the Water for Life project, which aims to engage FBOs on the defence of natural resources. It will be developed as a result of workshops in a community in the Amazon and additional research. It will identify the main challenges of the communities on assessing and managing water and the rooted alternatives developed by them. The case studies will then be used as subsidiary information for further activities of the project, namely theological reflections and online course for faith leaders.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The workshop and study will support communities to increase awareness of their challenges related to water management and ability of carrying out (with partners) an informed advocacy agenda. 
Theological reflections will be rooted in concrete experiences of communities in the Amazon.</narrative>
  </description>
